{
  "stem": "3605.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, my father was in such a situation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As I mentioned, that was my father and my brother work for a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- and he used to send them to Piotrkow, where the factories were, to take the orders, and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my brotherly usually went.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he had perfect Aryan looks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He had blue-grey eyes and blond hair.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he walked out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And immediately, he took off the armband.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We were wearing white armbands and a blue star of David-- Magen David was on them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "You couldn't go anyplace.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "All the people in the ghetto were Jews, but we still had to wear those armbands, to degrade us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So, not that it is a degradation to wear a Star of David, but the way we wore-- wore them, to point out that we are Jews, and the Germans thought that we are equal to vermin, not to a people that brought to the world good things-- like the face of one god, the 10 Commandments that is the moral code for humanity.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And comparative to the population that we were in each country, we had very wonderful cultural contributions.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But this was never pointed out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was pointed out-- things that were untrue and-- and things that-- we were used as scapegoats.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And those armbands we had to wear like an armband of shame.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So if we go out, right away, they should notice us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And if they caught Jews out there--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's see.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother had a permission to go out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But he was supposed to wear the armband, so people could see a mile away that he is a Jew on a permit.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
